Rule Learning, Probabilistic Methods. 

Rule Learning is present in the text as the paper discusses the use of decision trees as a benchmark for classifier learning. Decision trees are a type of rule-based classifier. 

Probabilistic Methods are also present in the text as the paper discusses the use of probabilistic classifiers, such as Naive Bayes, as part of the benchmark. The paper also discusses the use of probabilistic measures, such as accuracy and error rates, to evaluate the performance of the classifiers.
